This paper is about image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new architecture for CNNs, which involves residual connections and channel attention mechanisms, indicating that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, suggesting that it may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
